title: Claude Monet Irises Keychain
description:
Keychain developed from Claude Monet’s Irises, 1914-17, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Irises is one of a series of large paintings Claude Monet undertook during World War I experimenting with familiar motifs on an ever-expanding scale.

  • Dimensions: 1.25 x 1.875 x .25 in.
  • Materials: Metal, Card Stock, Resin.
